;Observation schedule
;From ONTARGET entries in the AFT (NuSTAR.aft.SOC). Slews occur between End time and following Start time
;
;Start - ONTARGET start time of observation (UTC)
;End - ONTARGET end time of observation (UTC)
;sequenceID - ID for the observation, linked to HKplot directory for the observation
;Name - Name of the target
;J2000_RA - J2000 epoch Right Ascension (degrees)
;J2000_Dec - J2000 epoch Declination (degrees)
;offset_RA - Commanded Spacecraft Right Ascension (degrees)
;offset_Dec - Commanded Spacecraft Declination (degrees)
;Saa - Solar aspect angle (degrees). The value in the middle of the observation, will change during the observation.
;Aim - Aimpoint for the target in DET1 coordinates [X,Y] mm
;CR - Expected Count Rate of target above background (events/s 5-80 keV)
;Orbits - Number of full orbits in the observation
;Exp - Approximate exposure for the observation (ksec). ONTARGET duration minus Earth occultation and SAA passages.
;Notes - STELLAR mode will include a change in yawOffset of approximately 1 degree/day resulting in a small motion
; of target on the detector. INERTIAL mode holds the attitude of the spacecraft fixed (default).
;
;Start End sequenceID Name J2000_RA J2000_Dec offset_RA offset_Dec Saa Aim CR Orbits Exp ACS_mode
